definition.value: A  methoxyflavanone that is  flavanone substituted by methoxy groups at positions 5, 6, 7 and 8 and a hydroxy group at position 4'.
A methoxyflavone that is flavone substituted by methoxy groups at positions 5, 6, 7, 8, 2', 4' and 5'.
A  methoxyflavone that is flavone substituted by methoxy groups at positions 5, 6, 7, 8, 2' and 5'.
A methoxyflavone that is flavone substituted by methoxy groups at positions 5, 6, 7, 8, 3' and 5'.

A tetrahydroxy-monohydroxy-flavone, with the four hydroxy groups at C-3',-4',-5 and 6, and the methoxy group at C-7.  It has been isolated from a number of plant species, including Eremosparton songoricum, Rabdosia japonica and Ruellia tuberosa.
A tetramethoxyflavone that is flavone substituted by am ethoxy group at position 4' and methoxy groups at positions 5, 6, 7 and 8.
A methoxyflavone that is flavone substituted by methoxy groups at positions 5, 6, 7, 8, 3', 4' and 5'.
A tetramethoxyflavone that is flavone substituted by methoxy groups at positions 5, 6, 7 and 8 and an acetoxy group at position 4'.
A dimethoxyflavanone that is flavanone substituted by methoxy groups at positions 5 and 7 and hydroxy groups at positions 6 and 4'.

A pregnane sterol that is 5beta-pregnane carrying hydroxy groups at positions 3alpha and 21, oxo group at position 11, a double bond between positions 17 and 20 and the D-ring of the steroid has been expanded to a 6-membered ring by the addition of a methylene group.
